Day 9: Breaking things on purpose

Officially moved into Phase 2 today and built the synthetic damage generator. Wrote the logic to randomly mask words, drop characters, and delete phrase spans to perfectly mimic the missing ink and torn pages our OCR engines will eventually spit out.

Hooked the script up to a live Wikipedia dump and successfully generated a test batch of 10,000 training pairs (clean target vs. damaged input) straight into a CSV using Pandas. Hit a weird Windows socket error at the end because the streaming connection didn't want to close when the script finished, but patched it up cleanly with a system exit.

The dataset pipeline is fully operational. Tomorrow, we build the evaluation metrics to actually grade the AI, and then we crank the dial up to generate the full 500k master dataset.